• to future-proof the UK’s creative industries by protecting art subjects from exclusion from state educational programs;
• to provide, through a new schooling model, vocational learning to individuals who wish to pursue a creative career – regardless of their academic achievement;
• to promote UK talent and the creative industries both at home and abroad;
• to establish conditions under which respect for these obligations are maintained by British law;
• to promote creative collaboration between organisations;
• to unite our strength to maintain influence and social significance;
• to grant immunity for all arts subjects against future education budget cuts;
• to ensure, by the acceptance of principles and the institution of methods, that the vocational teaching of creative subjects will remain forever a right of every British citizen;
• to secure investment in the promotion of all UK creative industries for the economic and social advancement of all peoples.
